<HEADLINE>
<P>
HANS COHN; COLLECTOR OF ARTWORKS FROM ANCIENT CIVILIZATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hans Cohn, 90, an investment banker and art collector who showed his extensive 
collections of glass and other works from ancient civilizations at the Los 
Angeles County Museum of Art and elsewhere over the past several years.Cohn and 
his wife, Varya, amassed antiquities from Greek, Roman, Etruscan and Egyptian 
cultures that were shown at LACMA in 1990, and the museum opened a permanent 
installation of the Cohns' collection of ancient glass pieces the same year. 
Cohn began collecting in the 1930s in his native Germany but lost many 
treasures when he fled to the United States before World War II. He had been a 
LACMA trustee since 1983. In Los Angeles on Monday. 
</P>
