<P>
DAVID OSBORN; FORMER U.S. AMBASSADOR TO BURMA, CAREER DIPLOMAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Osborn, 73, a former U.S. ambassador to Burma whose mastery of Japanese 
and Chinese helped resolve various diplomatic crises.Osborn's 31-year career 
with the Foreign Service included multiple postings in Japan, as well as 
assignments in Taiwan and Hong Kong. It culminated with the ambassadorship to 
Burma from 1974 to 1978. His language skills were invaluable during 
interrogations of Japanese prisoners in World War II, during war crimes trials 
and as a participant in diplomatic talks with Chinese Communists in the 
mid-1950s. In San Diego on Sept. 16 of injuries incurred in a bicycle accident. 
