<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAN'T YOU GUYS EVER RIP RAIDER COACHES? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When the Raiders were beaten by San Francisco and Seattle, The Times' 
sportswriters placed the entire responsibility on the players. Never will any 
of your writers criticize the coaching staff.Not once last year did reporters 
for Raider games place any responsibility on Art Shell and his coaching staff. 
</P>
<P>
 The reason is clear: Your writers fear what Raider management will do to their 
player access. The Raiders have made it clear, they will tolerate criticism of 
players, but never the coaches, and Times writers adhere to this policy. How 
can we know that you are our trusted agents at the battle front who won't 
automatically place the responsibility for a loss on the soldiers rather than 
on the generals? 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT W. GREER 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
