<TEXT>
<P>
 Phil Simms said he will listen to offers from Arizona Cardinal Coach Buddy 
Ryan or anybody else who wants him to return to the NFL as a quarterback. He 
just hasn't had any offers yet. 
</P>
<P>
 Simms' agent confirmed Friday that Arizona had called to talk about his 
client, but David Fishof said no offer had been made. 
</P>
<P>
 "I still don't know anything, and I still haven't talked to anybody from out 
there," Simms said from Franklin Lakes, N.J. "If somebody wants to contact me, 
I will listen." 
</P>
<P>
 Simms, who was not offered a contract by the New York Giants this season, said 
he hadn't spoken with his agent Friday, but "he told me they were going to 
talk, so I assume they have. I just don't know at this point." 
