<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; 1 SUSPECT IN SLAYING OF YOUTH SURRENDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One of two men sought in the fatal stabbing of a 17-year-old El Modena High 
School junior at a Trask Avenue mobile home park surrendered to police 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Keith E. Zavala, 19, walked into the police station at 1:30 p.m. with his 
attorney and was arrested on suspicion of murder, assault with a deadly weapon 
and auto theft. 
</P>
<P>
 Zavala, a resident of the Meadowlark Mobile Estates park where the stabbing 
took place Sept. 19, was booked into the Orange County Jail and held on 
$250,000 bail, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Luis Ramirez died at UCI Medical Center after being stabbed in the neck 
in a dispute involving three men and a woman. One of the men, Jose Rodriguez, 
20, of Santa Ana was treated for stab wounds and released from the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 After Ramirez and Rodriguez were stabbed, police said, Zavala and Miguel de 
Jesus Silva, a 23-year-old resident of the park, fled in Ramirez's red 1981 
Mustang, which was later found abandoned in Santa Ana. Police are still seeking 
Silva. 
</P>
</TEXT>
