<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ALISO VIEJO; ALISO NIGUEL HIGH TO BE DEDICATED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capistrano Unified School District officials today plan to dedicate Aliso 
Niguel High School. 
</P>
<P>
 The dedication comes more than a year after the $50-million campus opened its 
doors. 
</P>
<P>
 Because of construction delays caused by rainstorms, the school was forced to 
open last fall despite being only half built. 
</P>
<P>
 The facility has been touted as a "school of the 21st Century." 
</P>
<P>
 The dedication ceremony begins at 1 p.m. in the school theater. There will 
also be tours and food and beverages in the school stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 A 6 p.m. concert will feature the Drifters and the Coasters. Tickets are $3 
for adults and $1 for children 12 and younger. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds from the concert will benefit the Aliso Niguel High School 
Parent-Teacher-Student Assn. The school is at 28000 Terrace View Drive, in 
Aliso Viejo.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
