<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEACHERS TO DISCUSS EXCHANGE EXPERIENCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three American Fulbright Exchange teachers who taught in Europe last year will 
discuss their experiences at a meeting of the Thoreau Society at 4 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The speakers are: Anaheim kindergarten teacher Vivian Santibanez, who spent 
last year at a primary school in London; Karen Alms, who teaches German and 
literature at Laguna Hills High and spent last year in Gluckstadter, Germany; 
and English teacher Doris Blake of Woodbridge High in Irvine, who taught last 
year in Ipswich, England. 
</P>
<P>
 The Thoreau group meets in Community Room 200 in the Irvine Marketplace. 
</P>
