<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAMILY HOMELESS AFTER FIRE AT FOURPLEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire of suspicious origin left one family homeless Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire began about 8 p.m. on the second floor of a fourplex in the 16500 
block of Regina Circle and quickly spread to the ceiling and roof, Battalion 
Chief Duane Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
 A 14-year-old girl living in one of the four units was treated for smoke 
inhalation and taken to Huntington Beach Medical Center, according to Fire 
Department spokesman Randy Goodman. 
</P>
<P>
 It took 33 firefighters a little more than 20 minutes to control the blaze. 
</P>
