<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; PEDESTRIAN, 28, IS SHOT IN THE FACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 28-year-old man was hospitalized in critical condition Friday after being 
shot in the face by an unknown assailant as he walked on a Santa Paula street, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Raymond Samaniego of Santa Paula was walking with a female companion in the 
100 block of Santa Maria Street when he heard someone shout from a passing car, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Samaniego turned to look and was struck once in the face, police said. The 
bullet lodged in the back of his head. 
</P>
<P>
 Samaniego was transported by private vehicle to Santa Paula Hospital, than 
transferred to Ventura County Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said there was no known motive for the assault. An investigation was 
continuing. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
