<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; MATER DEI DOMINATES HAWTHORNE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mater Dei scored 38 points in the last eight minutes of the first half and 
rolled to a 52-11 victory over Hawthorne Friday night at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The second-ranked Monarchs (3-0) showed no weaknesses, forcing seven 
turnovers, dominating special teams play and were nearly flawless on offense. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawthorne, ranked second in Division II, stayed with Mater Dei through the 
first quarter, but collapsed in the second. 
</P>
<P>
 The assault began when Rod Perry caught a 43-yard touchdown pass over the 
middle from John Flynn, giving the Monarchs a 14-0 lead with 8 minutes 11 
seconds left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 After Hawthorne failed to gain a first down, Perry set up Mater Dei's third 
score when he returned the punt 27 yards to the Cougar 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Three plays later, Steve Bodnar scored his second touchdown of the game on a 
14-yard pass from Flynn. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei then hammered Kelvin Hunter on the ensuing kickoff, separating him 
from the ball, which was recovered by Douglas Odom at the Hawthorne 15. 
</P>
<P>
 On the next play, David Castleton caught a 15-yard scoring pass to make it 
28-0 with 4:03 remaining in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei lineman Brad Williams swatted away a pitch out, picked it up and 
returned it 15 yards for the touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawthorne then fumbled the kickoff and Flynn hit Castleton on an 11-yard slant 
for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Another Cougar turnover set up the last of the second-quarter barrage as 
Patrick Shinnefield booted a 49-yard field goal as the first half whistle 
sounded giving Mater Dei a 45-0 lead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
