<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; OWENS' RUNS RUN TROY RAGGED AS BREA 
ROLLS TO 28-7 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY ALTOBELLI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jerome Owens ran for 183 yards and scored three touchdowns Friday night to 
lead Brea-Olinda past Troy, 28-7, in a nonleague game at Brea-Olinda High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wildcats (2-1) scored 28 points after falling behind, 7-0, after Troy 
scored on its first possession.But the Warriors (2-1) were unable to stop Owens 
all night and the junior running back scored Brea's final three touchdowns to 
blow the game open, scoring on two three-yard runs and a one-yard plunge. 
</P>
<P>
 Owens' longest run from scrimmage was 27 yards. He also completed a 31-yard 
pass to Andy Wirz during the Wildcats' final scoring drive. During the 10 play, 
88-yard drive, Owens was responsible for 72 of those yards. 
</P>
<P>
 In a battle of running backs, Troy's Larry Montgomery ran for 93 yards in 22 
carries. The teams combined to pass for only 125 yards in 20 attempts. 
</P>
<P>
 Troy's touchdown came on a two-yard run by Ryl Relatores. Brea answered with a 
38-yard run by quarterback Matt Kalcevich, who rushed for 84 yards in nine 
carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Troy's last threat was stopped by an interception at the goal line by Mike 
Beamer with three minutes remaining in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Kalcevich, who threw for only 54 yards on seven attempts, had runs of 38 and 
32 yards and finished with 84 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wildcats shut down Troy's passing game, limiting the Warriors to 40 yards 
in 11 attempts. TONY ALTOBELLI 
</P>
</TEXT>
