<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; GARDENA SERRA OVERWHELMS DANA HILLS, 
33-11 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON H. REID, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Something happened to that successful formula Dana Hills used in the first 
half of its nonleague game Friday night against Gardena Serra. 
</P>
<P>
 And when Serra realized it had the Dolphins (0-3) on the run, it turned up the 
pressure. 
</P>
<P>
 The speedy Cavaliers rallied to rout Dana Hills, 33-11, in front of 
approximately 3,000 at Serra. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills led, 11-6, at halftime, but Serra shut out the Dolphins, 27-0, in 
the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cavaliers (2-1) relied on several big plays in the second half, with 
running backs Ademole Turner and Ricky Boyer providing the biggest. 
</P>
<P>
 Turner returned a fumble by the Dolphins' Randy Hein 98 yards for the go-ahead 
touchdown with 7 minutes 6 seconds to play in the third quarter. That gave 
Serra a 12-11 lead, which is all it would need. Turner also scored Serra's 
first touchdown with a 50-yard run in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Boyer gained 134 yards in only eight carries, and dashed the Dolphins' hopes 
of a rally with a 94-yard touchdown run in the fourth quarter. The extra point 
gave Serra a 27-6 lead with 10:06 remaining in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Dolphin quarterback Scott Maynard completed 12 of 28 passes for 118 yards with 
one touchdown and one interception. He combined with John Morgan on a 40-yard 
touchdown pass with 1:22 to play in the second quarter. Eric Knip completed a 
two-point conversion to Ilan Katz to give Dana Hills its 11-6 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Knip opened the game's scoring with a 40-yard field goal at the 2:32 mark of 
the first quarter. After halftime, however, Dana Hills could not move the ball 
consistently. 
</P>
<P>
 Randy Hein rushed 15 times for 57 yards to lead Dana Hills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
