<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; MISTAKES COST OCEAN VIEW; CENTURY WINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Century turned three Ocean View turnovers into touchdowns and knocked off the 
Seahawks, 39-13, in a nonleague game Friday at Westminster High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View did not get past the Century 40-yard line until the final seven 
minutes of the game and managed only 149 yards in offense.The Seahawks have 
lost 32 consecutive games, the longest losing streak in the state. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither team scored in the first quarter, but the Centurions took command in 
the second quarter with three touchdowns in a seven-minute span. 
</P>
<P>
 Century's Richard Roa set up the first, recovering a fumble by running back 
Calvin Silva at the Seahawk 6. Robert Villegas plunged in from the one three 
plays later and Century led, 7-0. 
</P>
<P>
 On their next possession, Centurion quarterback Stanley Villanueva completed a 
57-yard pass to Ignacio Vega to the Ocean View 22. The Centurions scored when 
Villanueva found Jorge Rodriguez in the flat for a 20-yard touchdown. Oscar 
Salcedo increased the Century lead, intercepting a Ted Norman pass on the next 
play from scrimmage and returning it 31 yards for a 19-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Century padded the lead to 32-0 in the third quarter. Villanueva connected 
with Rodriguez on a 40-yard scoring play, and Luis Ramirez added a touchdown on 
a 31-yard fumble return. ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</TEXT>
