<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; ROBERSON PASSES MARINA PAST SUNNY HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LYNCH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marina quarterback Matt Roberson passed for 133 yards and a touchdown, and 
running back Micah Harrison rushed for 49 yards to lead the Vikings to a 23-12 
victory over Sunny Hills Friday night in a nonleague game at Buena Park High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings (3-0) scored on their first possession of the game as kicker Peter 
Mignosa drilled a 42-yard field goal. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers stumbled in the first quarter, however, committing a series of 
errors. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills quarterback Greg Garand fumbled two snaps and had two passes 
intercepted in the quarter. The Lancers had six turnovers in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings capped a six-play, 50-yard drive after Garand's second fumble as 
Roberson scrambled five yards for the touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers scored with one second left in the first half, as Gerand ran a 
10-yard sweep into the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sunny Hills' offense gained momentum in the third quarter, putting 
together an 11-play, 75-yard drive. Garand scored again, on a one-yard dive 
into the end zone, to bring the Lancers to within four points. 
</P>
<P>
 On a fourth-and-three play from midfield, the Vikings gained a first down on a 
fake punt. On the next play, Roberson hit wide receiver Joe Borzoni with a 
35-yard touchdown pass to cap a four-play, 46-yard drive. MICHAEL LYNCH 
</P>
