<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCGRAW DRIVES FOR FIVE AS LAGUNA HILLS ROLLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brendan McGraw rushed for five touchdowns as Laguna Hills beat Las Vegas 
Silverado, 47-8, Friday night at Mission Viejo High. 
</P>
<P>
 McGraw, who rushed 22 times for 164 yards, has scored 12 touchdowns in three 
games this season.All have come rushing.  
</P>
<P>
 The Hawks (2-1) scored on their first possession when McGraw ran up the middle 
for 15 yards and a 6-0 lead with 8 minutes 38 seconds left in the first 
quarter.  
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills made it 12-0 when McGraw went 32 yards down the left sideline 
with 5:35 left in the first quarter.  
</P>
<P>
 McGraw scored two more times before halftime as Laguna Hills built a 26-0 
lead. With 10:37 left in the half, McGraw went off tackle for a four-yard 
touchdown run. He then went in from three yards out with 30 seconds left in the 
half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hawks scored on their first possession in the third quarter when McGraw 
ran off tackle from four yards out for a 33-0 lead. After backup quarterback 
Corey Pardoe threw an 18-yard touchdown to Jay Johnson with 5:27 left in the 
third, Hawk Coach Steve Bresnahan pulled the rest of the starters. 
</P>
<P>
 Led by Pardoe, the second string players made the score 47-0 as time ran out 
in the third quarter. Vijay Goel scored from one yard out. 
</P>
<P>
 Silverado (0-4) scored its only touchdown on a five-yard run by quarterback 
Toby Smeltzer with 8:20 left in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
