PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; ORANGE LUTHERAN POUNCES ON LAGUNA BEACH 
ERRORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The mistakes came early and all too often Friday night for Laguna Beach, as 
visiting Orange Lutheran rolled to a 45-7 nonleague victory at Guyer Field. 
</P>
<P>
 Two lost fumbles early in the first quarter put the Artists behind, 14-0, six 
minutes into the game.Orange Lutheran quarterback Joe Juliano opened the 
scoring with a 10-yard run. Minutes later, the Lancers recovered a second 
fumble on the Artists' 25, to set up Matt Stratton's eventual one-yard plunge. 
</P>
<P>
 Juliano teamed with Dan Young on a 50-yard pass play to put Orange Lutheran in 
scoring position at the Artists' 19. Stratton's 16-yard run set up his second 
touchdown -- from the one for a 21-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Stratton rushed for a game-high 146 yards as the Lancers rolled up 360 yards 
in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran's Carlos Glade returned another loose ball to the Artists' 30. 
Three plays later, Orange Lutheran's Che Holloway ran five yards for a 
touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Juliano had a hand in the final 14 points of the first half, running in a 
score from the 20, and throwing for another. His 17-yard strike to Aaron Kenny 
came after Orange Lutheran called a timeout with eight seconds left in the 
half. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach scored in the third quarter on Aaron Chesley 11-yard run. 
Stratton's 38-yard field goal closed out Orange Lutheran's scoring. RICK 
CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
