</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trailing 24-14 at halftime, Valencia rallied for two touchdowns to defeat El 
Dorado, 28-24, in a nonleague game Friday night at Bradford Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tigers drove 92 yards in 10 plays to open the second half.Quarterback Joe 
Secoda capped the march with a four-yard scoring pass to tight end Chris 
Roussin, which brought Valencia to within 24-20 with 7:05 remaining in the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Running back Damian Askins scored the winning touchdown on a six-yard run with 
8:13 left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado got off to a fast start when Richie Williams returned the opening 
kickoff 99 yards for a touchdown. Valencia tied the score at 7-7 on its first 
drive of the game, when Secoda scored on a two-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams scored his second touchdown of the game on a two-yard run. It didn't 
take long for Valencia to tie the score again, as Askins returned the ensuing 
kickoff 97 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Stephens kicked a 40-yard field goal with just more than 11 minutes 
remaining in the first half to give the Golden Hawks a 17-14 lead. Quarterback 
Mike Marcicola scrambled for a 24-yard touchdown run with 36 seconds remaining 
in the first half to give the Golden Hawks their 10-point lead at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado drove nearly seven minutes on its final possession, but Valencia's 
Jermaine Gray intercepted a Marcicola pass. DALE RUHE 
