<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; SMITH, SERVITE UPSET FOOTHILL IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jerry Smith scored six goals and Bill Howard added three to lead Servite, the 
fourth-ranked water polo team in Orange County, to an 11-8 upset victory over 
second-ranked Foothill in a South Coast Tournament quarterfinal Friday at 
Tustin High. 
</P>
<P>
 Servite went ahead, 4-3, at the half and never trailed.Goalkeeper Trevor 
Dallas had 13 saves for the Friars (7-1). Brian Brown scored four for Foothill 
(4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In other quarterfinal games: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 13, Villa Park 5 -- Third-ranked Corona del Mar overpowered 
seventh-ranked Villa Park with its tight defense, allowing Villa Park 13 shots. 
Neil Hueston had four goals for Corona del Mar (3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach Wilson 12, Newport Harbor 6 -- Gabe Wyatt scored five goals and 
Graham Harvey recorded six saves for Newport Harbor (2-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In quarterfinals of the Rowland Heights Rowland tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 9, San Bernardino 6 -- Tad Murphy had six goals to lead 
fifth-ranked Brea-Olinda (6-0). Eric Matthews added two goals and Tim Bischel 
had 10 saves for the Wildcats. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 9, Magnolia 2 -- Kendall Benson scored six goals for El Dorado 
(2-2). Benson also scored the winning goal in overtime in a second-round 
victory over Cerritos. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 12, Estancia 11 -- Senior Bret Trezise scored nine goals for 
Saddleback, including the game-winner with 10 seconds left. Trezise has 57 
goals this season for Saddleback (6-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 3, Dana Hills 0 -- Melissa Schutz had 20 kills and Sara 
Fairborn had 14 for host Newport Harbor (8-0), ranked No. 1 in the county. 
Eighth-ranked Dana Hills is 9-2. 
</P>
