<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SYLMAR; COLLEGE EXTENSION COURSES OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What do computers and pepper spray have in common? 
</P>
<P>
 You can learn to use both during Los Angeles Mission College's Community 
Extension fall program, which features more than 160 workshops and seminars. 
</P>
<P>
 Beginning Oct. 15, most workshops will be held at Granada Hills High School, 
located at 10535 Zelzah Ave. in Granada Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Offerings include courses in business opportunities, careers, computers, 
exercise, travel, foreign languages, music, performing arts, holiday 
decorations and other subjects. 
</P>
<P>
 Also scheduled are three pepper spray self-defense training and certification 
workshops conducted by an officer from the Los Angeles Police Department and an 
administration of justice instructor at Mission College. 
</P>
<P>
 A fall catalogue of classes can be obtained through the extension office, 
located in Veteran's Memorial Park, 13000 Sayre St. in Sylmar. The phone number 
is (818) 364-7387. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
