PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; POLICE PROBE PLAYER-COACH ALTERCATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From staff reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Long Beach Police Department is investigating an alleged assault Thursday 
night by a Los Alamitos High football player on defensive backs coach Steve 
Scully, a police spokesman said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. Torbin Beith said a report has been filed on the incident that occurred 
during the Griffins' 23-16 victory over Carson at Long Beach Veterans Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Police and Los Alamitos school officials are withholding the player's name 
because he is a juvenile. 
</P>
