<HEADLINE>
<P>
JENKINS' 356 YARDS LEADS HUENEME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ronnie Jenkins blistered Camarillo High by rushing for 356 yards and three 
touchdowns in 20 carries to lead Hueneme to a 47-29 nonleague victory Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenkins scored on runs of 90, 65 and 48 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The 5-foot-11, 160-pound junior had amassed 294 yards by halftime to give the 
Vikings (2-1) a 28-15 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo (1-2) scored first on Roth Valencia's 34-yard run in the first 
quarter to cap a six-play, 66-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
 But Viking quarterback George Jones struck back quickly, connecting with 
Rashod Cousins for a 13-yard touchdown play after a 40-yard run by Jenkins. 
Jones added a one-yard scoring run late in the first quarter to give Hueneme a 
lead it didn't relinquish. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia rushed for 168 yards in 25 carries. MIKE JOHNSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
