<P>
CRESCENTA VALLEY SURVIVES BURBANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BARTLETT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brett Baker's 28-yard field-goal attempt with two seconds remaining missed 
wide left, allowing unbeaten Crescenta Valley to escape with a 15-14 victory 
over Burbank Friday night at Burroughs High. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley (3-0) overcame a 14-0 halftime deficit behind senior Chris 
Hedrick, who gained 102 yards in 28 carries. Hedrick moved the Falcons to 
within 14-9 with a one-yard touchdown run in the third quarter, and gave them 
the lead on a one-yard run with 1 minute 36 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Baker of Burbank (1-2) scored on a 22-yard run in the second quarter. 
He caught two passes for 38 yards on the final drive. 
</P>
