<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BRESNAHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sylmar High Coach Jeff Engilman encapsulated his team's performance with one 
word. 
</P>
<P>
 The word, an adjective more likely heard in the locker room than the 
classroom, seemed surprising considering his team's 32-0 victory over El Camino 
Real in a nonleague game Friday night at Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't feel good right now," said Engilman, soured by his team's poor 
offensive showing in the first half. "I'm going to go home and have some Tums." 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar running back Durell Price had 158 yards in 10 carries and two 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 The Spartans (3-0) held El Camino Real (1-2) to 79 yards. MIKE BRESNAHAN 
</P>
