<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGHLAND EARNS FIRST WIN, 40-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jason Carr and Ladarral Hollingsworth carried the load offensively for 
Highland High and the Bulldogs rolled to an easy 40-6 victory Friday over 
Verdugo Hills in an intersectional game at Quartz Hill High. 
</P>
<P>
 Carr opened the scoring with a 55-yard reception on a halfback option from 
Hollingsworth on the third play of the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Carr completed 10 of 12 passes for 187 yards and two touchdowns, and scored on 
runs of 24 and 22 yards in the second quarter to give the Bulldogs a 33-0 
halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 To close out the Bulldogs' 19-point first quarter, Hollingsworth scored on a 
66-yard pass play and a 41-yard run. He finished with 102 yards rushing in 
seven carries. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bulldogs (1-2) scored on their first five possessions and limited the Dons 
(0-2-1) to 16 yards in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Verdugo Hills scored its only points on its first possession of the second 
half on a six-yard pass from David Kelly to Ryan Brouchet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
