<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; BUENA TRAMPLES NEWBURY PARK STREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG MEADE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Carr and Josh Cross of Buena High ran roughshod over Newbury Park's 
Ventura County-record winning streak, combining to rush for 254 yards and lead 
the Bulldogs to a 28-0 nonleague victory Friday night at Ventura High. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park (2-1), which won the Southern Section Division III championship 
with a 14-0 record last season, had its streak snapped at 16.The Panthers had 
not lost to a Ventura County school since the 1991 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena (2-1) controlled the line of scrimmage, moving the ball consistently 
behind 6-foot-6, 270-pound tackle John Raymond. 
</P>
<P>
 "My backs would come back to the huddle and say, 'Those holes are huge. Our 
coach could even get through them,' " Raymond said. 
</P>
<P>
 On its first possession, Newbury Park drove to the Buena four, but Carr 
intercepted a pass. The Bulldogs drove 96 yards in nine plays, capped by Carr's 
seven-yard scoring run. 
</P>
<P>
 Carr finished with 127 yards in 17 carries, including a 30-yard scoring run. 
</P>
<P>
 Cross gained 125 yards in 15 carries. Nathan Coyle scored Buena's other two 
touchdowns on one-yard runs. Buena junior quarterback Glenn Dudley passed for 
99 yards, completing nine of 20 with one interception. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Justin Vint led Newbury Park in rushing with 46 yards in seven 
carries. The Panthers managed only 146 total yards. GREG MEADE 
</P>
</TEXT>
