games between these neighborhood rivals, but rallied with two second-half 
touchdowns to surprise the Regents. 
</P>
<P>
 Courtney Blunt's one-yard run, followed by Luis Saldero's extra point, put 
Birmingham (3-0) ahead halfway through the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Reseda (1-2) scored first on Michael Oxx's six-yard run and went ahead, 13-0, 
on quarterback Matt Rutter's 23-yard pass to Alonso Arreola in the second 
quarter. Arreola's first-quarter extra-point try bounced off the right upright. 
