<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHAMINADE SACKS GRANADA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRIAN CHALEW, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chaminade High dominated every phase of its 28-8 intersectional victory over 
Granada Hills on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 A strong rushing attack, a long touchdown pass and a defensive effort that 
included nine sacks left little doubt why the Eagles have started the season 
with a 3-0 record. 
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade quarterback Tom Racius completed 15 of 29 passes for 282 yards, 
including a 70-yard scoring pass to senior Dino Dinielli. The score gave the 
Eagles a 21-0 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Dinielli caught four passes for 131 yards and also forced a fumble in the 
second quarter while recording one of the Chaminade sacks. 
</P>
<P>
 Granada Hills quarterback Bryan MacLean completed 12 of 25 for 208 yards, but 
the sacks gave him minus-66 rushing yards. MacLean hit Eric Carpenter with an 
18-yard pass in the third quarter for the Highlanders' only touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Giovannettone scored Chaminade's first two touchdowns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
