<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEE CARRIES ROYAL OVER VENTURA, 16-13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LANCE O'FALLON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Running back Jerome Lee rushed for 185 yards in 19 carries, including a 
55-yard touchdown run, to lead Royal High to a 16-13 victory over Ventura in a 
nonleague game Friday night at Moorpark College. 
</P>
<P>
 Royal (2-1) jumped to a 16-0 lead, scoring on its first three possessions. 
</P>
<P>
 The first touchdown came 1 minute 40 seconds into the game when Christian 
Broussard, who finished with 46 yards in five carries, scored on a 12-yard run. 
The drive was highlighted by Lee's 61-yard run to the Ventura 12. 
</P>
<P>
 After forcing Ventura (0-3) to punt, Royal marched to the Ventura 26 but 
settled for a 45-yard field goal by Matt Pitstick. 
</P>
<P>
 The Highlanders, who held Ventura to 145 yards, again forced a punt. Royal 
marched 95 yards in seven plays and capped the drive on a 55-yard touchdown run 
by Lee. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cougars got on the board with 45 seconds to play in the first half when 
quarterback Erik Olson (five of 11 for 69 yards) combined with Aaron Davis on a 
21-yard pass. 
</P>
<P>
 After Ventura's Ramsey Jay returned the second-half kickoff 78 yards, Davis 
scored on a two-yard run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
