<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; CSUN GOES THE LIMIT BUT LOSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A strong rally by the the Cal State Northridge women's volleyball team fell 
short Friday night as the Matadors lost a five-game, nonconference match at the 
University of San Diego, 15-5, 15-5, 12-15, 12-15, 20-18. 
</P>
<P>
 Aimee Stone had 24 kills and 12 digs and Kathleen Shannon had 49 assists to 
lead Northridge (7-6), which could not overcome the 20th-ranked Toreros. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego (9-4) was paced by Jennifer Wrightson (24 kills, 12 digs), Amy 
McMahon (12 kills, 10 blocks) and Luann Petix (53 assists). HIGH SCHOOL WATER 
POLO 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake 13, Oxnard 7 -- David Brock scored 10 goals to lead the Warriors in a 
nonleague match at Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake scored five goals in the first quarter to take a 5-1 lead. 
</P>
