DIGEST: RAIN POSTPONES SEASON FINALE AT VENTURA RACEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Racing fans must wait a week to see Ventura Raceway's points champions crowned 
in the Street Stock and Mini Stock divisions after Friday's season finale was 
postponed because of wet grounds. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fourth rainout in seven years, and the third this season at the 
quarter-mile clay oval on the Ventura County Fairgrounds.The finale is 
scheduled for next Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Bill Bartels of Los Angeles and James Weston of Santa Barbara are tied for 
second place in Street Stock competition, 30 points behind defending champion 
Paul Moore of Oak View. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Mini Stock class, 15 points separate first-place Richard Webster of 
Camarillo and challenger Tim Gill of Somis. Miscellany  
</P>
<P>
 The Northridge Little League team will visit with patients at the West Los 
Angeles Veterans Administration Medical Center today at 9:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The players, 11- and 12-year-olds who won the national championship last month 
in Williamsport, Pa., will tour the facilities after receiving an instructional 
briefing. 
