WEEKEND TV; A NEW SEASON FOR SEVERAL TOP SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some of TV viewers' favorite series return with a flourish this weekend, 
including CBS' "Murder, She Wrote," starring Angela Lansbury, Sunday at 8 p.m. 
on Channels 2 and 8.  
</P>
<P>
 Tonight, NBC offers two season-opening episodes of "Empty Nest," beginning at 
8 p.m., and also "Sisters," at 10 on Channels 4, 36 and 39. 
</P>
<P>
 CBS' "Dr. Quinn, Medicine Woman," starring Jane Seymour, starts anew at 8 
p.m., followed by "Hearts Afire" at 9:30 p.m. and "Walker, Texas Ranger" at 10 
p.m. ABC counters with the season premiere of "The Commish" at 10 p.m. on 
Channels 7, 3, 10 and 42. 
</P>
<P>
 On Sunday, Nickelodeon's "Rocko's Modern Life" begins a new season at 5:30 
p.m. N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
